readability_reflection: I find string concatenation more readable because it naturally causes a separation between parts of the string using the + symbol and spaces.
comprehension_debugging: Yes, interpolation does lead to a small challenge when it is nested, as it is a bit hard to parse due to my lack of experience with it.
preference_rationale: String concatenation, as it is what I am used to, and find that spacing out the different parts of the string helps me see what needs to be put where.
learning_curve: Yes, my familiarity of string concatenation helped me parse strings with it a bit quicker, and my inexperience with interpolation did cause me to have some uncertainty when parsing it.
